Several Palestinian leaders, including Mahmud Abbas, are expected in Paris the following day.
Arafat's wife, Suha, criticizes Palestinian leaders for attempting to seize power while he is alive.
Arafat is allowed to leave his headquarters in Ramallah for medical treatment in France.
Conflicting reports on Arafat's condition emerge, with some claiming he is dead.
Israeli and Palestinian officials reach an agreement on funeral arrangements.
Arafat's possible burial in Gaza or Ramallah is discussed.
Egypt offers to host a funeral service for Arafat to spare Arab leaders from Israeli security measures.
